A Ugandan was charged on Monday with registering as a Kenyan voter.Walukaga Jalaldin was charged alongside Lucas Odundo in a Mombasa court, and they both denied four charges of obtaining registration as a voter falsely.They are accused of unlawfully obtaining registration of a Kenyan ID in the name of Salim Jalal at the chief registrar of persons&rsquo; office in Ganjoni, Mombasa county, on October 19, 2016.Their accomplices are said to be on the run.Odundo was said to have conspired with Jalaldin to obtain the documents.Odundo is charged with pretending to be Jalaldin&rsquo;s father to enable the suspect to obtain a Kenyan registration card by the name of Salim Jalal Okungu.He is also charged with unlawfully permitting Jalaldin to use his ID card.Jalaldin said he did not lie to get an ID and insisted he is a Kenyan and has the right to obtain an ID and to vote.&ldquo;I used to be a Ugandan citizen but I also obtained Kenyan citizenship and that makes me a Kenyan as per the law,&rdquo; he said.Chief magistrate Julius Nang&rsquo;ea (pictured) released them on Sh500,000 bond with an alternative of Sh300,000 bail.The matter will be mentioned on February 27.